<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 13 at 4:58PM EDT until July 13 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 530 PM EDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN PORTAGE...SOUTHEASTERN MEDINA...WESTERN STARK...
SOUTHERN SUMMIT AND NORTHEASTERN WAYNE COUNTIES...
At 458 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Doylestown, or
9 miles southwest of Akron, moving southeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.
Locations impacted include...
Akron, Canton, Massillon, Barberton, Green, Wadsworth, Tallmadge,
North Canton, Rittman, Mogadore, Doylestown, Hartville, Creston,
Navarre, New Franklin, Norton, Fairlawn, Canal Fulton, Lakemore and
Seville.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
